investor of a Party means a Party or state enterprise thereof, or a national or an enterprise of a Party, that attempts to make, is making, or has made an investment in the territory of the other Party; provided, however, that a natural person who is a dual national shall be deemed t o be exclusively a national of the State of his/her dominant and effective nationality; 

monopoly means “monopoly” as defined in Article 16.9 (Definitions); 

